                <p><bibl><ptr target="#bacchielli1996a"/>, p. <citedRange>28</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>46.2210</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>084200</citedRange></bibl>.</p> 
                   <p>Cf.  <bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1998"/>, pp. <citedRange>277-279</citedRange></bibl> 
                    (=<bibl><ptr target="#gasperini2008"/>, p. <citedRange>418</citedRange></bibl>) and
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>1999.622</citedRange></bibl>;
                       <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.31</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Δεῖνις">Δεῖνις</name> <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Εὐρυφῶν">Εὐρυφῶνος</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>Deinis fils d'Euryphon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Deinis son of Euryphon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Deinis figlio di Euryphon.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The base should have supported a half-statue of the funerary goddess.</p>
                <p>For the tomb, see <bibl><ptr target="#thorn2006"/>, p. <citedRange>342 </citedRange>and fig. 217.</bibl></p>
            </div></body>
